Cell.Text: S|So you're the one that got out of Helgen, eh? I guess if you've seen a dragon before we can use you, even if you are half-trained. | Where do you think you'll be most useful - scouting ahead or supporting the rest of my men?
Well? You going to scout ahead or travel with me?
G|Sorry, I've got urgent business with the General.
[S] G|All right. We're assembling in the courtyard. Come on.
[S] G|Sounds good. We'll meet up outside Fort Hraggstad.
I knew I could count on Captain Metilius. But is there more you're not telling me?

Node.Caption: MQ104TulliusOutroA1: Fort Hraggstad is destroyed, but the dragon is dead.

Cell.Text: Rikke was just trying to explain this to me. What are you talking about?

Node.Caption: MQ104TulliusOutroA2: Turns out I may be something called "the Dragonborn".

Cell.Text: [S] G|Legate Rikke's been saying the same thing. She's quite worked up about it.

Node.Caption: MQ104TulliusOutroB2: That's just what the men called me.

Cell.Text: [S] G|So, Legate Rikke was right.

Node.Caption: MQ104TulliusOutroB1: When the dragon died, I absorbed some kind of power from it.

Cell.Text: Perhaps you do. A medal at the very least. We'll have to create a new one, or maybe dust off a very old one. "Dragonslayer" or some such. | But is there more you're not telling me?

Node.Caption: MQ104TulliusOutroA3: I killed the dragon. I think I deserve a promotion.

Cell.Text: [S] I suppose you may as well go and see what these Greybeards want with you. | But don't forget that you're still in the Imperial Legion.
Well, you came back alive. Legate Rikke here seems to think you must have some astounding news. | Tell me, what happened at Fort Hraggstad?
G|Captain Metilius is in command of the Fort Hraggstad expedition. You'll get your orders from him.
G|Not now, soldier.
G|We'd better go make sure that bastard is really dead. Collect us a trophy or something to bring back to the General.
G|Scatter and get behind cover! We need to hurt it, somehow! If you've got a bow or spells, now would be a good time to use them!
G|I hope they're right about you. You sure did for that dragon. That's good enough for me.
G|I'm proud to be your battle-brother, Dragonborn. We'll win for sure with you on our side.
G|I can't believe we actually killed a dragon!
G|Dragonborn... it's an honor.
G|With you on our side, the Stormcloaks don't stand a chance.
G|Is it really dead?
G|Come on, I want a better look at that thing.
G|We taught that dragon not to mess with the Legion, eh?
G|I'm glad you're on our side.
[S] G|Get under cover! The dragon - it's still around somewhere!
G|They say you've got the luck of Stendarr. Hope some rubs off on the rest of us.
G|That dragon should have known better than to pick a fight with the Legion.
G|My buddy's stationed at Fort Hraggstad. I hope he's all right.
G|I doubt any of us are coming back from this mission.
G|It's time to teach this dragon a lesson.
G|I hear you were at Helgen and lived to tell about it. That ain't nothing.
G|Captain Metilius will get us through this if anybody can.
G|You really think we can kill a dragon?
G|We'd better keep moving. Who knows what that dragon is doing to our brothers at Fort Hraggstad.
G|I hope the fort holds out until we get there.
G|This doesn't look good.
G|Stendarr guard us, did it kill them all...?
G|We'd better find out what's happened.
G|We'd better keep moving.
G|Good luck at Fort Hraggstad. I hope you get there before it's too late.
G|Shut it. I want to hear what the Captain's saying.
[S] If you really are Dragonborn, then Skyrim needs you. Go to High Hrothgar and talk to the Greybeards.
G|The General needs to talk to you. And so do I, as soon as he's finished with you.
That may be true, but I ordered Captain Metilius to bring back proof. You'd best report back to your Captain at once.
